  "issue_title": "bug: Stream Link does not abort",
  "issue_body": "### Provide environment information\n\n```\r\n  System:\r\n    OS: Windows 11 10.0.22631\r\n    CPU: (32) x64 AMD Ryzen 9 7950X 16-Core Processor\r\n    Memory: 46.84 GB / 63.65 GB\r\n  Binaries:\r\n    Node: 20.13.1 - C:\\P\\apps\\nodejs\\node.EXE\r\n    Yarn: 1.22.19 - C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Yarn\\bin\\yarn.CMD\r\n    npm: 10.5.2 - C:\\P\\apps\\nodejs\\npm.CMD\r\n  Browsers:\r\n    Edge: Chromium (126.0.2592.81)\r\n    Internet Explorer: 11.0.22621.3527\r\n  npmPackages:\r\n    @trpc/client: next => 11.0.0-rc.436+fbb4a2fb4\r\n    @trpc/server: next => 11.0.0-rc.436+fbb4a2fb4\r\n    typescript: ^5.5.0 => 5.5.3\r\n```\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nThe AbortController signal seems ignored by Stream Links with async generators.\r\n\r\nWe'd expect an interruption on the server side, and on the client side, but packets continue to be produced by the async generator, flow to the client, and the client keeps awaiting and receiving them.\r\n\r\nI don't know what the correct behavior would be, but right now the signal seems to be completely ignored on both ends.\n\n### Link to reproduction\n\nhttps://github.com/enricoros/trpc-repro-stream-unabort\n\n### To reproduce\n\nIn summary:\r\n1. The client creates a Stream Link, and queries with a `{signal: ac.signal}`, like this (minimal):\r\n```typescript\r\nconst trpc = createTRPCClient<AppRouter>({\r\n  links: [unstable_httpBatchStreamLink({url: 'http://localhost:3000',})],\r\n});\r\n\r\nconst ac = new AbortController();\r\n\r\nconst iterable = await trpc.examples.iterable.query(undefined, { signal: ac.signal });\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. The server implements a procedure with an async generator, like this (minimal):\r\n```typescript\r\n    iterable: publicProcedure.query(async function* () {\r\n      for (let i = 0; i < 8; i++) {\r\n        await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 500));\r\n        yield i;\r\n      }\r\n    }),\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. We would expect both the server and the client to be aborted, but execution continues on both.\r\nThis is the output:\r\n![image](https://github.com/trpc/trpc/assets/32999/b4175a3f-7e46-486f-81e4-7008a4014e86)\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_\n\n### \ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc67\u200d\ud83d\udc66 Contributing\n\n- [ ] \ud83d\ude4b\u200d\u2642\ufe0f Yes, I'd be down to file a PR fixing this bug!",
